    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-03-10T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-03-10T18:00:00-05:00" n="591"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d591">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">791.003/79b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Persia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Philip</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-03-10T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 10, 1928—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. Department’s 16, March 3, 5 p.m. A conversation on the subject mentioned
                    therein took place with the Italian Ambassador on March 8. Greatly interested,
                    he promised to cable immediately to the Italian Government and felt sure that it
                    would appreciate greatly the suggestions of the Department and would very gladly
                    instruct your Italian colleague to keep closely in touch with you.<note n="19"
                        xml:id="d591fn19">On March 10, 1928, the Secretary of State also cabled the
                        Ambassador in Italy (No. 26), summarizing the conversation and adding that
                        “Similar conversations have been held with the British, French, and German
                        Ambassadors.” (File No. 791.003/79c.)</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Embassy in Germany reports instructions have been sent the German Minister in
                    Persia for full cooperation with you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
